    <body>
        <ab xml:id="SC1">
            <s type="orig">ⲭ̅ⲡ̅ⲑ̅ ⲥⲩⲛ [ⲑ̅ⲱ̅] ⲣⲁϩ̄ⲟⲙⲉ
            </s>
            <s type="trans" xml:lang="en">‘Michael. With (God), I have begun [ἄrxoμai].’</s>
            <note>The first Greek word of the sermon following the present one in the
                Sinai ms. is ἀrxόμeja. Browne reads [ⲭ̅]ⲡ̅ⲑ̅ ⲥⲩⲛ [ⲡ]ⲣⲁϩ̄ⲟⲙⲉ·, Miqaήl, sύμpraxόn
                μoi. See Browne<note place="bottom" n="1">Gerald M. Browne, “Notes on Old Nubian Texts (IV–V),” Sudan Texts Bulletin 7 (1985):
                    1.</note> and Browne<note place="bottom" n="2">Gerald M. Browne, Old Nubian Textual Criticism, Beiträge zur Sudanforschung Beiheft
                        8 (Vienna: Verein der Förderer der Sudanforschung, 1998), 27.</note>.</note>
        </ab>
        <ab xml:id="SC2">
            <s type="orig">ⳟⲥ̄ⲉⲛⲟⲕⲗ̄ ⲓ̈ⲱⲁⲛⲥⲏ ⲕⲟⲗⲥ̄ⲧⲁⲛ[ⲧ]ⲓ̣[ⲛⲟ]ⲡⲟⲗⲛ̄ ⲁⲣⲭⲏⲉ̄ⲡ̣[ⲓ]ⲥⲕⲟⲃⲟⲥⲁⲇⲉⲛⲟ̣ⲩ̣
                ⲟⲛ ⲁⲕⲗ̄ ⳟⲁⲡⲕ̄[ⲟⲁⲇ]ⲉⲛⲁⲛⲛⲁ [ⲥ̄ⲧ]ⲁⲩⲣ[ⲟ]ⲥⲟⲩ ⳟⲟⲕⲕⲟ̣ⲛ̣ⲕ̣ⲓ̣ⲛ ⲟⲣⲱⲥ̣[ⲉⲛ ⲥⲁⲗⲁⲗⲟ·] ⲧⲗ̄ⲗⲛ̣̄
                ⲧⲱⲕ̣[ⲛ̄]ⲁⲩⲉ̄ⲗⲟ̣ⲕ̣ⲟ̣ ⲁ̄ⲙ̣ⲏ̣ⲛ̣ⲣⲉ·</s>
            <s type="parse">ⲟⲛ-ⲧⲁⲕ-ⲣ-ⲁ-ⲅⲟⲩⲉ-̄ⲕⲉ ⲙ-ⲛⲁ ⲗ-̣̄ⲇⲛ̄ⲛⲉ· ⲙⲛⲁ ⲡⲉⲥⲁⲣⲣⲉ·</s>
            <s type="roman">ŋis-enok-il iōansē kolistantinopol-in arkhēepiskobos-a-denal(notOU?) on akil ŋapi-ko-a-denan-na istaurosou ŋok-kon-k-in orōse-n sal-a-lo till-in tōkinaue-loko amēn</s>
            <s type="gloss">holy-COMP-DET John Constantinople-GEN, archbishop-PRED-CONJ and mouth gold-ADJ-PRED-CONJ-GEN cross glory-ADJ-?-GEN praise-GEN word-PRED-FOC God-GEN peace-LOC.through amen</s>
            <s type="trans" xml:lang="eng">‘(This is the word) of praise of the Holy Cross of the holiest John, Archbishop of Constantinople and golden-mouthed. Through the peace of God, Amen.’</s>
            <note/>
        </ab>
        <ab xml:id="SC3">
            <s type="orig">ⲟⲛⲧⲁⲕⲣⲁⲅⲟⲩⲉ̄ⲕⲉ ⲙⲛⲁ ⲗ̣̄ⲇⲛ̄ⲛⲉ· ⲙⲛⲁ ⲡⲉⲥⲁⲣⲣⲉ·</s>
            <s type="parse">ⲟⲛ-ⲧⲁⲕ-ⲣ-ⲁ-ⲅⲟⲩⲉ-̄ⲕⲉ ⲙ-ⲛⲁ ⲗ-̄ⲇⲛ̄ⲛⲉ ⲙⲛⲁ ⲡⲉⲥ-ⲁⲣ-ⲣ-ⲉⲣⲉ·</s>
            <s type="roman">on-tak-r-a-goue-ke mn-a il-d-in-n-e mn-a pes-ar-r-e</s>
            <s type="gloss">love-PASS-PRS-PRED-PL.PRED-2PL what-QUOT say-INTEN-CAP-PRS-1SG.PRED what-QUOT say-INTEN-PRS-1SG.PRED</s>
            <s type="trans" xml:lang="eng">‘Beloved! What could I say? What shall I speak?’</s>
            <note>Notes The scribe misinterprets aorist subjunctive lalήsw as future indicative,
                translating with ⲡⲉⲥⲁⲣⲣⲉ.</note>
        </ab>
        <ab xml:id="SC4">
            <s type="orig">ⳟⲁⲉⲓⲁ̄ ⲟⲩⲕ ⲟ̄ⲕⲓⳝⲁⲣⲣⲉ·</s>
            <s type="parse">ⳟⲁⲉⲓ-ⲁ̄ ⲟⲩ-ⲕ ⲟ̄ⲕ-ⲓⳝ-ⲁⲣ-ⲣ-ⲉ</s>
            <s type="roman">ŋaei-a ou-k ok-ij-ar-r-e</s>
            <s type="gloss">who-QUOT 2PL-ACC call-PLACT-INTEN-PRS-1SG.PRED</s>
            <s type="trans" xml:lang="en">‘What shall I call you?’</s>
            <note>Notes The following affirmative forms in -ⲙⲁ are all dependent on the verb
                ⲟ̄ⲕⲓⳝⲁⲣⲣⲉ.</note>
        </ab>
        <ab xml:id="SC5">
            <s type="orig">ⲧⲓⲕⲁⲛⲉⲅⲟⲩⲉ̄ⲙⲁ ⲥⲉⲛⲁ· ⲙⲉⲛⲉⲛⲛ[ⲟⲛ] ⲕⲟⲣⲟⲥⲉⲅⲟⲩⲉ̄ⲙⲁ·</s>
        </ab>
